  "prompt": "What does \"designation\" mean on a form?",
  "response": "On a form, the term \"designation\" typically refers to a title, label, or specific role assigned to an individual or entity. It helps to categorize or identify the person's position, function, or status within a particular context. For example:\n\n- **Job Title**: If the form is related to employment, \"designation\" might mean your job title, such as \"Manager,\" \"Engineer,\" or \"Consultant.\"\n- **Role or Position**: In organizational contexts, it could indicate your role, like \"President,\" \"Secretary,\" or \"Member.\"\n- **Identifier**: It might also refer to a specific identifier, such as a project designation, account designation, or membership level.\n\nThe exact meaning depends on the context of the form, so it\u2019s always a good idea to review the instructions or examples provided.",
